authors: Siticone Technology, Russell Chidhakwa, Ilham Mutaqin
description:
Siticone Desktop UI version 3 (part of the Siticone Framework Suite) builds upon the success of its predecessor, offering an enhanced set of features and improvements to elevate your .NET and Windows Forms UI/UX design experience.

Designed to streamline developer productivity, Siticone Desktop UI version 3 remains at the forefront of the .NET UI development landscape. With its futuristic, high-performance, and sleek user interface components, it empowers developers to deliver exceptional user experiences effortlessly, even with minimal programming experience, all while maintaining a reasonable budget.

Embedded within the .NET Ecosystem and adhering to industry-accepted naming and design conventions, Siticone Desktop UI version 3 ensures a smooth learning curve for developers. Once installed, you can unlock its true potential with just a few simple clicks.

Adding Siticone Desktop UI version 3 to your project is straightforward:

    Install the library.
    Open the Visual Studio Toolbox and create a new tab, such as "Siticone Desktop UI Components."
    Right-click and select "Choose items."
    Browse for the installed library in the "bin" folder and add it.
    Drag and drop any Siticone Controls onto your Winform, and you're good to go!

To learn how to make the most of Siticone Desktop UI version 3, we highly recommend watching tutorials and video demos available on our YouTube channel: Link to the YouTube channel.

Minimum System and User Requirements:

    Siticone Desktop UI version 3 is compatible with C# and VB.NET programming languages within a Windows Forms Application Development Environment.

Minimal Technical Requirements:

    Microsoft .NET Framework 4.0 or higher.
    Visual Studio 2012 or later.

Developer Requirements:

    Basic knowledge of C# or VB.NET programming languages (both are advantageous).
    Familiarity with Windows Forms application development system (Winforms).

For more detailed information and getting started guides, please visit our website: Link to Siticone Framework website.

If you require any support or have further inquiries, you can reach out to us via email at support@siticoneframework.com.

Additionally, we provide live support on our website: Link to live support.

We wish you a productive and fulfilling UI/UX development journey with Siticone Desktop UI version 2!
